This paper discusses the development and deployment of constraint programming applications using an extended Prolog language, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also covers aspects of combinatorial problem solving, mathematical programming, and search techniques, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions an integrated development environment and interfaces for embedding into host environments, which are relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and machine learning (cs.LG).
